title: Ethereum price retreats amidst strategic whale moves - AMBCrypto English
summary: Two large Ethereum whales have sold off a total of over 28,000 tokens in recent days, causing the price of ETH to retreat. This has led to a net outflow of ETH from exchanges, but there has been a reversal in the netflow as of writing. The whales' sales have been attributed to a strategic profit-taking move, rather than a market dump. The 60-day Market Value to Realized Value Ratio (MVRV) of Ethereum has also decreased, suggesting that the profit derived from the sales of ETH has experienced a substantial reduction. The Ethereum price has been weakening, with a 1.7% decrease in value and the RSI line approaching the point of crossing below the neutral line, suggesting a weakening of the initial bull run.

title: The active supply of Bitcoin and Ethereum is at record lows - The Block
summary: The active supply of Bitcoin and Ethereum has reached record lows, according to data from The Block. Only 30.12% of Bitcoin's supply has moved in the past year, down from a peak of 59% in 2017-2018. Similarly, 39.15% of Ethereum's supply has changed hands in the past year, down from 86% in 2016-2017. The inactive supply of Bitcoin has reached a record high of 41.42%, while the five-year active supply has fallen from 83% to 70.13%. Despite the low activity, transactions on the network are nearing their peak.

title: Crypto Whales Sell Off Ethereum (ETH)-Based Altcoin Before Massive 40% Correction: On-Chain Data - The Daily Hodl
summary: Crypto whales sold off millions of dollars worth of yearn.finance (YFI) on Saturday before it sharply corrected by over 40%, according to on-chain data. One wallet deposited $5.8 million worth of YFI to crypto exchanges, while a whale sold 96 YFI for $1.23 million before the price drop. Another wallet associated with the decentralized exchange aggregator 1inch (1INCH) sold its UNI tokens for $2.13 million at a loss. YFI is now trading for $9,408, up 2% in the last 24 hours, while UNI is trading for $5.09, nearly the same price as when the 1inch Investment Fund sold its holdings.

title: Ethereum price dilemma or buy signal before 60% rally - FXStreet
summary: Ethereum price is consolidating inside an ascending triangle on the weekly chart, with a potential breakout forecasting a 43% upswing to $2,943. The price could also reach $3,186, which is the next MRI resistance level, representing a 60% gain.

title: Ethereum (ETH) Bullish Whales Coming Back With Enormous Longs - U.Today
summary:
Here is a summary of the article in 256 tokens or less:

Ethereum (ETH) whales are showing bullish signs, with one whale repaying debt and another moving funds to cold storage for long-term holding. These actions indicate a strategic vote of confidence in ETH's price appreciation potential. These moves underscore a sustained bullish sentiment and a long-term investment perspective, but the market remains vigilant as extensive selling by these whales could prompt a market pullback.

title: Bitcoin Surges After Javier Milei Elected President Of Argentina — Ethereum, Dogecoin Seen In Green: Anal - Benzinga
summary: Bitcoin surged after Javier Milei was elected President of Argentina, a libertarian candidate who supports Bitcoin. The cryptocurrency market gained momentum, with Bitcoin increasing by 2.31%, Ethereum by 2.78%, and Dogecoin by 2.33%. Milei's election is seen as a positive development for the cryptocurrency market, as he has been critical of the country's central bank and has expressed support for Bitcoin. Other cryptocurrencies also saw gains, with Render, Kaspa, and FTX Token leading the top gainers list. The global crypto market cap decreased by 1.49% in the past 24 hours, but the U.S. equity futures showed a minimal change. Analysts believe that Bitcoin is forming a clear range and could potentially move slightly lower before dipping just below $36,000.
